Preconditions:
The input string `colors` should not be null.
The input string `colors` should not be empty.
The input string `colors` should only contain lowercase letters.
The input array `edges` should not be null.
The input array `edges` should not be empty.
The input array `edges` should only contain valid indices of the `colors` string.
The input array `edges` should not contain duplicate edges.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value.
The returned value should be the largest color value of any valid path in the given graph.
If the graph contains a cycle, the method should return -1.